<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-107] Bug in serialize and collate logic in the DefaultEventHandler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-107</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a bug in the serialize and collate in the DefaultEventHandler, that uses the map() API on a hashmap to convert a sequence of messages to a ByteBufferMessageSet, based on the compression configs. The usage of the zip() API after the map() API on a hashmap, has the side effect of reordering the mapping between the keys and the values. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12519065">KAFKA-107</key>
            <summary>Bug in serialize and collate logic in the DefaultEventHandler</summary>
